  <h2>Measure the Space Before Choosing Storage</h2>
  <p>
    Home office storage often fails because the product fits the items but not
    the room. Before buying, measure the width beside the desk, the depth under
    or beside the desk, the height available under the desktop and the walkway
    around the work zone.
  </p>
  <p>
    Also check the distance from the chair to nearby drawers or shelves, the
    clearance needed for chair movement, wall space for shelving and floor area
    for freestanding storage. A drawer unit may look compact online but still
    block a chair, doorway or cupboard.
  </p>
  <p>
    This is especially important in small bedrooms, apartments and shared living
    areas. If the desk still needs adjustment, check the{" "}
    <a href="/guides/home-office-desk-setup-what-to-measure-before-you-buy/">home office desk setup guide</a>{" "}
    before committing to storage that depends on the current desk position.
  </p>

  <figure class="article-figure article-figure--diagram">
